This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the performance of deep neural networks in classifying complex data and introduces a new metric for measuring class separability in the hidden layers of these networks. Additionally, the paper discusses the tuning of hyper-parameters, which is a common topic in machine learning. 

The paper also touches upon the topic of neural networks, which falls under the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). 

Furthermore, the paper discusses the classification of complex data sets, which is a common topic in computer vision, falling under the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

The paper also discusses the self-organization of data transformations during training, which is a topic in artificial intelligence, falling under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Finally, the paper discusses the application of the Contrastive Divergence method, which is a common topic in natural language processing, falling under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language).
